sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Webhook as Training Operator Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Controller as Training Operator Controller
    participant Kubelet as Kubelet
    participant Registry as Container Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Master as Training Master Pod<br/>23456/TCP
    participant Worker1 as Training Worker Pod 1<br/>23456/TCP
    participant Worker2 as Training Worker Pod 2<br/>23456/TCP
    participant S3 as Object Storage (S3)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,S3: Flow 1: Training Job Creation

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply -f pytorchjob.yaml<br/>Auth: User credentials
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-pytorchjob<br/>mTLS (K8s API Server)
    Webhook->>Webhook: Validate job spec
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation response
    K8sAPI-->>User: PyTorchJob created

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch PyTorchJob CRs<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: PyTorchJob event
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Pods (master + workers)<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Services<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create PodGroup (gang scheduling)<br/>ServiceAccount Token

    Note over User,S3: Flow 2: Training Job Execution

    Kubelet->>Registry: Pull training image<br/>Pull Secret
    Registry-->>Kubelet: Image layers
    Kubelet->>Master: Start master pod
    Kubelet->>Worker1: Start worker pod 1
    Kubelet->>Worker2: Start worker pod 2

    Master->>S3: Load dataset<br/>AWS IAM / Cloud credentials
    Worker1->>S3: Load dataset<br/>AWS IAM / Cloud credentials
    Worker2->>S3: Load dataset<br/>AWS IAM / Cloud credentials
    S3-->>Master: Dataset
    S3-->>Worker1: Dataset
    S3-->>Worker2: Dataset

    Master->>Worker1: Initialize distributed training<br/>TCP 23456 (PyTorch rendezvous)
    Master->>Worker2: Initialize distributed training<br/>TCP 23456

    loop Training iterations
        Worker1->>Master: Gradient sync<br/>Framework-specific protocol
        Worker2->>Master: Gradient sync<br/>Framework-specific protocol
        Master->>Worker1: Updated weights
        Master->>Worker2: Updated weights
    end

    Master->>S3: Save trained model<br/>AWS IAM
    S3-->>Master: Model saved

    Master->>Master: Training complete
    Worker1->>Worker1: Training complete
    Worker2->>Worker2: Training complete

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update PyTorchJob status<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: Job status: Succeeded

    Note over User,S3: Flow 3: Metrics Collection

    Prom->>Controller: GET /metrics<br/>ServiceAccount bearer token
    Controller-->>Prom: Operator metrics (job count, status, duration)
